<div class="container">
    <h1>Proof Of Work</h1>
    <h4>The "work" consists of finding a number (called nonce) for which, when append to the input, produces a hash containing a certain number of leading zeros.</h4>
    <h4>For instance, if we set the number of leadind zeros to 4, the result of hash(input + nonce) must start with "0000".</h4>
    <h4>The bigger the number of leading zeros is, the less likely the hash is going to match and therefore the longer the "work" will take.</h4>
    <h4>With the number of leading zeros set to 1, click on the 'nonce' box and  press the 'up' key â†‘ of your keyboard to increment it. Notice that the hash gets updated each time. Keep incrementing the nonce until the hash has 1 leading zero. Here you are actually doing the "work".</h4>
    <h4>Then set the nonce back to 0 and try with higher number of zero.</h4>
    <h4>When you get tired of it, just press the "Find a match" button.</h4>
    <h4>Finding a match when talking about Bitcoin is called "Mining"</h4>
